{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770322168,"nonce":"Hpan4u9HDdONiaN0i7wpkmfISbs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oqNwT","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/174","origin":"github"},"title":"Add shellcheck to CI pipeline for script validation","message":"## Problem\n\nShell scripts can have subtle bugs that aren't caught until runtime. We currently don't have automated linting for bash scripts.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd shellcheck to GitHub Actions CI pipeline.\n\n## Implementation\n\nUpdate `.github/workflows/ci.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nname: CI\n\non: [push, pull_request]\n\njobs:\n  shellcheck:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Run shellcheck\n        uses: ludeeus/action-shellcheck@master\n        with:\n          scandir: './.agent/scripts'\n          severity: warning\n          \n  validate-docs:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Check for stale doc references\n        run: |\n          python3 .agent/hooks/check_doc_references.py\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n- Catch common bash pitfalls early\n- Enforce consistent style\n- Prevent merging scripts with syntax issues\n- Combined with doc validation (issue #172)","files":null}]}